# perl-base CVEs (Debian 13.6 base image dependency, not invoked by our code):
#
# CVE-2026-13221 - Perl regex trie 16-bit overflow -> silently wrong matches.
#                   Requires compiling an attacker-crafted regex via Perl.
#                   Our Lambda runs only Python; perl-base is a transitive
#                   dpkg dependency of python:3.12-slim, never executed.
#                   Fixed upstream in Perl 5.43.10; re-check on next base
#                   image bump.
CVE-2026-13221

# CVE-2026-42496 - perl-archive-tar path traversal via crafted symlinks.
#                   We never call Archive::Tar or any Perl code; not reachable.
CVE-2026-42496

# CVE-2026-8376  - Perl regex heap buffer overflow, 32-bit builds only.
#                   Container runs linux/amd64 (64-bit); not applicable, and
#                   still requires invoking Perl, which we never do.
CVE-2026-8376
